title: Boys Soccer: Warren Hills named top seed in H/W/S Tournament
text:
Boys Soccer: Warren Hills named top seed in H/W/S Tournament Lauren Knego @laurenknego 7:16 p.m. EDT October 1, 2015 Boys soccer 1 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
The Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex Boys Soccer Tournament has been seeded and Warren Hills earned the No. 1 seed. 
The Blue Streaks (6-2), which have never won a tournament title, earned a bye into the quarterfinals, along with second-seeded Newton (6-0-3), third-seeded Phillipsburg (6-1-1) and No. 4 High Point (7-0-1). Defending champion North Hunterdon, which has won eight H/W/S titles, was named the No. 10 seed. 
The first round is set to start this Saturday, weather permitting, at the site of the higher seed. The second round is slated for Oct. 10 and the quarterfinals will be held Oct. 17. The semifinals are scheduled for Oct. 24 and the final will be on Oct. 31. 
Here is the bracket for the first round. 
17-Voorhees at 8-Sparta; 16-Belvidere at 9-Pope John; 13-Wallkill Valley at 12-South Hunterdon; 20-Kittatinny at 5-Lenape Valley; 14-North Warren at 11-Delaware Valley; 19-Sussex Tech at 6-Vernon; 15-Hackettstown at 10-North Hunterdon; 18-Hopatcong at 7-Hunterdon Central.
